CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 23, 1960, pg. 1 reads: "Auto Parade - As a prelude to the "Rebels" rally at Westinghouse High School auditorium, the "Rebels" staged an 108 car torchlight parade. in lead were Joseph Watts, parade marshall and candidate for committeemen in the Sixth District; Atty. Linn Washington, the candidate; Erroll Davis, "Rebels" campaign manager, and Attorney Washington's wife, Eunice, and their children."
TitMainTitle: Children in street in front of majorettes and marching band, during torchlight parade for 13th Ward "Rebels" rally, Brushton and Hamilton Streets, Homewood
